Depends: libgtk2-trayicon-perl, libgtk2-perl, gtklp, liblocale-gettext-perl, libglib-perl, perlmagick, libxml-simple-perl, libwww-mechanize-perl, libwww-perl, gnome-web-photo, libgnome2-perl, libgnome2-gconf-perl, imagemagick, libgnome2-wnck-perl, libx11-protocol-perl
Recommends: postr
Conflicts: 
Replaces: gscrot-plugins-bash
Provides: gscrot, gscrot-plugins-bash
Description: screenshot taking application written in perl and Gtk2
 Some of the features of GScrot
 - take a screenshot of your complete desktop or of a rectangular area
 - take screenshot directly or with a specified delay time
 - save the screenshots to a specified directory and name them in a convenient way (using special wild-cards)
 - fully integrated into the Gnome Desktop (TrayIcon etc.)
 - generate thumbnails
 - automatically reduce color depth
 - save and revert your settings
 - session collection
 - Upload your screenshots
 - Edit your Screenshots directly (simple drawing tool included)

